  "prompt": "How do I report identity theft?",
  "response": "To report identity theft, follow these steps:\n\n1. Contact the Federal Trade Commission (FTC)\n- File a report at IdentityTheft.gov\n- Create an official Identity Theft Report\n- Get a personalized recovery plan\n\n2. Contact your local police department\n- File a police report\n- Get a copy for your records\n\n3. Contact your bank and credit card companies\n- Report fraudulent transactions\n- Cancel compromised cards\n- Request new account numbers\n\n4. Contact the three major credit bureaus\n- Equifax: 1-800-525-6285\n- Experian: 1-888-397-3742\n- TransUnion: 1-800-680-7289\n- Place a fraud alert on your credit reports\n- Consider a credit freeze\n\n5. Contact other relevant organizations\n- Social Security Administration\n- DMV\n- Passport office\n- Medical insurance provider\n\n6. Monitor your credit reports and financial statements\n- Check for unauthorized activity\n- Request free credit reports annually\n\n7. Consider additional protection\n- Sign up for credit monitoring services\n- Use strong, unique passwords\n- Enable two-factor authentication\n\nRemember to document all communications and keep detailed records throughout the process.",
